text.tspan: On Monday, 09/09/2019, I had made a mistake on travel and went
to Surbiton rather than Sutton. I had to track backward, but the train did
not stop in Clapham Junction, went straight to Waterloo. I phoned up the
TFL and was told the trip from Clapham Junction to Sutton only cost £2.80
So for that day, I would have spent £3.0 for buses and £5.60 for train
return tickets. The TFL has a cap for £12.80 on OYSTER card and that's why
